@page "/"

<h3>Async ValidationDemo — Blazor Web App</h3>
<p>
    This app mirrors <strong>AsyncValidationConsoleDemo</strong> from the console samples and uses
    <strong>async</strong> validation with DI integration, two-phase execution, infrastructure error handling, and cancellation.
</p>
<p>
    Each page manually runs <code>Validator.TryValidateObjectAsync</code>, pushes results into the current
    <code>EditContext</code>, and lets Blazor await async I/O without blocking the server thread.
</p>

<div class="list-group">
    <a href="/registration" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenarios 1 &amp; 2:</strong> DI Service Resolution + Two-Phase Validation
    </a>
    <a href="/order" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 3:</strong> IAsyncValidatableObject — <code>Order</code> (cross-property)
    </a>
    <a href="/error-handling" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 4:</strong> Infrastructure Failure Handling
    </a>
    <a href="/cancellation" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 5:</strong> CancellationToken propagation with cancelable in-flight <code>Event</code> validation
    </a>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-success mt-3">
    <strong>Scenario 5 (CancellationToken):</strong> Now possible with async
    <code>Validator.TryValidateObjectAsync(..., cancellationToken)</code>.
</div>
